syn:
Here's a list of numbers. x = [386, 448, 496, 426, 248, 469, 70, 228, 16, 157, 82, 406, 246, 352, 163, 73, 336, 317, 241, 100, 359, 54, 17, 400, 213, 49, 50, 116, 262, 176, 61, 59, 14, 52, 118, 231, 218, 375, 55, 233, 223, 422, 150, 358, 394, 338, 403, 21, 7, 212]

Simulate the following algorithm with the list of numbers as input:

def f(arr):
    n = len(arr)
    for j in range(1, n):
        val = arr[j]
        i = j - 1
        while i >= 0 and val > arr[i]:
            arr[i + 1] = arr[i]
            i -= 1
        arr[i + 1] = val
    return arr
